description:
&lt;p&gt;East Lancashire Hospitals NHS Trust is looking to recruit a substantive Consultant Histopathologist on a full time (10 PA) basis, although applications from part-time applicants would be considered. The successful candidate will join a team of 10 Consultant Pathologists in a modern Cellular Pathology Department at Royal Blackburn Teaching Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an ambitious organisation that champions our people, encouraging team working and equipping them with new skills to continually improve services for patients. ELHT is a major referral centre for HPB, Head &amp; Neck and Urology Cancer Services and we also receive cancer resections from Colorectal, Breast and Gynae Units. We are a national screening unit for Breast and Bowel cancer screening patients. The Department is recognised for 4 Cellular pathology STs and in addition supported by 2 Senior Clinical Fellows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are expected to be experienced in all aspects of histopathology and non-gynae cytology and there are opportunities to develop special interests although experience in breast, urology, colorectal and skin pathology would be more beneficial to the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Hospital is situated close to the motorway networks and at close proximity to beautiful countryside of Ribble Valley and the Lake District and is 40 minutes away from Manchester.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Department of Cellular Pathology is UKAS accredited.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are expected to be experienced in all aspects of histopathology and non-gynae cytology and there are opportunities to develop special interests although experience in breast, urology, colorectal and skin pathology would be more beneficial to the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are required to process the FRCPath (or equivalent qualification) and have CCT or be within 6 months of obtaining this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Hospital is situated close to the motorway networks and at close proximity to beautiful countryside of Ribble Valley and the Lake District and is 40 minutes away from Manchester.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date for applications 22.11.2020&lt;/p&gt;
